description:
&lt;p&gt;Join our COVID response team and gain an insight into our response to the COVID crisis and the key role played by microbiology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Covid Lasham (Basingstoke) and Covid Mount (Winchester) units are part of the trust response to the Covid 19 pandemic. Operating a 7 day service from 07.30-19.00, we provide pre-procedure screening for patients as part of the trust restoration plan, as well as screening for our symptomatic staff and families to ensure a safe working environment for patients and staff at HHFT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition we operate a 7 day helpline service for staff where we provide guidance, clinical advice and support relating to Covid.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a 6 month secondment post with the opportunity for a registered Nurse to build on their clinical skills and work within a new multi-disciplinary team. There will be the opportunity to work with the microbiology team and gain an understanding of the trust response to Covid and how the Lasham unit has been an integral part of that response&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;IT skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empathy to patients’ needs and concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a multi-disciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to adapt to an evolving service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
